There was a stampede Wednesday night resulting from a fire outbreak at the Lagos campus of Law School located on Ozumba Mbadiwe Street, Victoria Island. According to an eyewitness account, the fire, suspected to have been caused by an electrical fault, started at 10 pm from the first floor of the 5-story building hostel housing the about 1500 law graduates on the Lagos campus. “The fire came with a big bang. There was a stampede in the hostel. A student jumped from the first floor where the fire started near the reading room. Other students ran out from their rooms stark naked. Rotary Club Of Lagos Reaffirms Commitment To Human Capacity… Passing Out Parade: NYSC Charges Corps Members To Remain Worthy… “People had asthma attacks and five people were injured bodily. One elderly woman who is a cleaner had her toe dislocated,” said our source. The fire was however contained when hostel security officials put off the main electrical server switch before the arrival of Fire Service some minutes later. The injured students are currently receiving medical attention at the school’s clinic. News Express also gathered that, apart from one big electric cable, no tangible property was destroyed as nothing was close to the place where the fire started from.